# Project Index

This file is a lightweight map for the agent. Read on demand when you need to know what's available.

## Always-on rules
- `.cursor/rules/00-memory-bank.mdc` — read `memory-bank/` at every conversation start.
- `.cursor/rules/03-boundaries.mdc` — hard constraints (never delete files, never push, etc.).

## Agent-requestable rules
- `.cursor/rules/01-coding-standards.mdc` — style, error handling, git conventions.
- `.cursor/rules/02-workflow.mdc` — how to start, execute, and complete a task.

## Skills (invoke via `/<slug>` or by description match)
- `/init-memory` — populate `memory-bank/` for a new project.
- `/update-memory` — sync `memory-bank/` with current state.
- `/plan` — plan before coding on multi-file tasks.
- `/commit` — stage + commit with pre-commit checks.
- `/review` — self-review uncommitted changes.
- `/checkpoint` — mid-session progress save to `memory-bank/activeContext.md`.
- `/status` — quick health check (git, memory, tests, lint).
- `/cleanup` — remove dead code and debug artifacts.
- `/stuck` — structured escalation when looping on the same error.

## Context files
- `memory-bank/projectbrief.md` — requirements and goals (foundation).
- `memory-bank/productContext.md` — why this project exists, UX goals.
- `memory-bank/activeContext.md` — current focus, recent changes, next steps.
- `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md` — architecture decisions.
- `memory-bank/techContext.md` — stack, dependencies, setup.
- `memory-bank/progress.md` — what works, what's left, known issues.